ADO-EKITI – The National Coordinator, Ekiti In Diaspora Develop­ment Initiative (EDDI), Dr. Ayodeji Malomo has dis­closed that the body was set to raise political awareness amongst the citizens of the state. Malomo, in a statement made available to journalists in Ado-Ekiti, explained that EDDI was conceptualised to promote and raise the political awareness of Ekiti citizens, which he said was present at low ebb. The statement urged Ek­iti people to take interest in knowing the quality of peo­ple aspiring to lead them and not to abandon the political space for those it termed as “rogues and criminals.” HOW NIGERIAN MEN CAN NOW NATURALLY STOP PREMATURE EJACULATION, LOW SPERM COUNT AND OTHER MEN'S SEXUAL NEEDS. MADAM ALWAYS WANTS IT BIGGER, STRONGER AND LONG-LASTING!!! Malomo posited that the political intervention of the EDDI was crucial at this mo­ment of Ekiti history when the state was about to hold another Governorship Elec­tion. According to him, Ekiti deserves the best political administration in the next political dispensation, say­ing those who have a passion for development should take a plunge into the race and rescue the people from their present parlous state. FG Announces Partial Closure Of Falomo Bridge For Six Weeks Rehabilitation From Sunday Osinbajo Urges Harnessing Of Nation’s Huge Population “The EDDI was conceptu­alised to promote a just, fair, and politically-engaged Eki­ti society, where all citizens, regardless of socio-economic status in the areas of educa­tion, income, and occupa­tion can be given a sense of belonging and treated as a respectable integral part of governance. “They must actively par­ticipate in politics and influ­ence public policy with the sole goal and objective of achieving good governance and delivery of the dividends of democracy to our people.